# Frontend guide — {{ProjectName}}

Flutter app using FVM, Riverpod, go_router, and golden tests. This guide applies because this project was initialized with `frontend=flutter`.

## App location

```
applications/{{ProjectNameLower}}/
├── lib/
│   ├── main.dart
│   ├── core/
│   │   ├── router/app_router.dart    # routes — CLI patches marker below
│   │   ├── api/api_connector.dart
│   │   └── theme/
│   ├── features/                     # one folder per screen/feature
│   └── generated/swaggen/            # generated OpenAPI client (do not edit)
├── swagger/swagger.json              # exported from .NET API
├── test/                             # widget + golden tests
└── pubspec.yaml
```

Requires **FVM** on PATH. Commands run via `fvm flutter …`.

## Adding a feature

```bash
agentGenCli new frontend-feature myfeature --withApi --yes
```

Creates `lib/features/myfeature/` (screen, provider, widget), generates `{feature}_service.dart`, and patches:

```dart
// lib/core/router/app_router.dart
// agentGenCli:routes
```

## API integration

When backend exposes an API for the feature:

1. Scaffold backend with `--withApi` first (if not done)
2. `agentGenCli project sync-openapi` — exports swagger, runs `build_runner`, regenerates `lib/generated/swaggen/`
3. Scaffold or update frontend feature with `--withApi`

Without `--withApi`, services contain TODO stubs pointing at the sync workflow.

## Code generation

```bash
# from applications/{{ProjectNameLower}}/
./generatefiles.sh          # build_runner for swagger client
fvm flutter gen-l10n        # also run by sync-openapi
```

## Testing

```bash
fvm flutter test
./test/update_goldens.sh    # or: fvm flutter test --update-goldens
```

Golden tests live under `test/features/`. Update baselines when UI changes intentionally.

## Do not hand-edit

- `lib/generated/swaggen/` — regenerate via `project sync-openapi` or `generatefiles.sh`
- Route list in `app_router.dart` at `// agentGenCli:routes` — use `new frontend-feature` or follow marker pattern
